# Claude Code & CLI Assistant Instructions

When working in this workspace, you must adhere to the design and technical rules defined in:
- [.agents/AGENTS.md](file:///.agents/AGENTS.md)

**📋 Implementation Plan:** Before implementing any feature, read [.agents/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md](file:///.agents/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md) for the phased build order, file map, dependency graph, and ponytail constraints.

Key constraints:
- Single-binary Wails (Go 1.22+ & React 19 + TypeScript + TailwindCSS v4).
- Go backend: strictly stdlib except gopsutil/wails. Safe command arguments, anti-zombie process group management, DPAPI/Secret Service keyring APIs.
- React frontend: virtualized lists for logs, ring-buffer capped state (1000 items), Framer Motion and Recharts.
- Git: Do NOT include `Co-authored-by` headers in Git commits.
- ponytail: full is active. YAGNI → stdlib → native → one line → minimum that works.
